Chelsea Says Anelka, Alex Can Leave in January Transfer Window

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 
2011-12-03T15:52:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-03/chelsea-says-anelka-alex-can-leave-in-january-transfer-window.html
Chelsea manager Andre Villas-Boas
said striker  Nicolas Anelka  and defender Alex have asked for
transfers, and will be allowed to leave the English Premier
League club next month.  “The conversation was fair and direct with the players,”
Villas-Boas said on the team’s website. The coach said the
players will continue to practice with the squad.  Alex joined Chelsea in 2007 after three years at PSV in the
Netherlands. The Brazilian played 115 times for the Blues, and
has scored 10 goals.  Anelka played for Real Madrid, PSG,  Manchester City , Bolton
and Arsenal before joining Chelsea in 2008. The Frenchman has
appeared 145 times for Chelsea and scored 59 times.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  